        "published": "2026-02-08",
        "description": "The JAY Login & Register plugin for WordPress is vulnerable to Privilege Escalation in all versions up to, and including, 2.6.03. This is due to the plugin allowing a user to update arbitrary user meta through the 'jay_login_register_ajax_create_final_user' function. This makes it possible for unauthenticated attackers to elevate their privileges to that of an administrator.",
        "title": "The JAY Login & Register plugin for WordPress is vulnerable to Privilege Escalation in all versions up to, and including, 2.6.03.",
        "attack_type": "Privilege Escalation",
        "cvss_max": 9.8
      },
      "cve": {
        "id": "CVE-2025-15027",
        "sourceIdentifier": "security@wordfence.com",
        "published": "2026-02-08T02:15:56.507",
        "lastModified": "2026-04-15T00:35:42.020",
        "vulnStatus": "Deferred",
        "descriptions": [
          {
            "lang": "en",
            "value": "The JAY Login & Register plugin for WordPress is vulnerable to Privilege Escalation in all versions up to, and including, 2.6.03. This is due to the plugin allowing a user to update arbitrary user meta through the 'jay_login_register_ajax_create_final_user' function. This makes it possible for unauthenticated attackers to elevate their privileges to that of an administrator."
          },
          {
            "lang": "es",
            "value": "El plugin JAY Login &amp; Register para WordPress es vulnerable a la escalada de privilegios en todas las versiones hasta la 2.6.03, inclusive. Esto se debe a que el plugin permite a un usuario actualizar metadatos de usuario arbitrarios a través de la función 'jay_login_register_ajax_create_final_user'. Esto hace posible que atacantes no autenticados eleven sus privilegios al de un administrador."
          }
        ],
